1
00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:07.880
Everything in London is incredibly more incredible than in Paris.

2
00:00:07.880 --> 00:00:10.920
All I need now is a minion to manicure my nails.

3
00:00:10.920 --> 00:00:13.480
The last one turned out to be more than disappointing.

4
00:00:13.480 --> 00:00:14.960
She totally betrayed me.

5
00:00:14.960 --> 00:00:18.440
So, if you're interested and above all loyal, apply now.

6
00:00:18.440 --> 00:00:20.880
You should stop watching these videos of Chloe.

7
00:00:20.880 --> 00:00:22.960
She's really not a good person.

8
00:00:22.960 --> 00:00:26.600
You're right, Mark.

9
00:00:26.600 --> 00:00:44.920
Are you sure we can't ride together like we used to?

10
00:00:44.920 --> 00:00:47.760
No, thanks, Daddy dear.

11
00:00:47.760 --> 00:00:51.240
If someone was bothering you at school, you'd tell me, right?

12
00:00:51.240 --> 00:00:52.480
Everything's fine, Dad.

13
00:00:52.480 --> 00:00:54.480
Some girlfriends are waiting for me at the bus stop.

14
00:00:54.480 --> 00:00:56.680
We're going to head to school together.

15
00:00:56.680 --> 00:00:58.600
I'm really glad you made new friends.

16
00:00:58.600 --> 00:01:12.800
Have fun, sweetheart.

17
00:01:12.800 --> 00:01:32.920
In the daytime, I'm Marinette, just a normal girl with a normal life, but there's something

18
00:01:32.920 --> 00:01:42.560
about me that no one knows yet, because I've got a secret.

19
00:01:42.560 --> 00:01:49.680
Marinette, I don't understand, why does this dinner absolutely have to take place tonight,

20
00:01:49.680 --> 00:01:51.760
otherwise it'll be a disaster?

21
00:01:51.760 --> 00:01:55.680
Because Tiki, tonight the Ho-Tin Star will be in conjunction with Jupiter.

22
00:01:55.680 --> 00:01:57.520
And what does that mean exactly?

23
00:01:57.520 --> 00:01:59.720
Well, according to Mom, it brings good luck.

24
00:01:59.720 --> 00:02:01.680
That's why I invited Adrian over tonight.

25
00:02:01.680 --> 00:02:06.800
Besides, since we've been going out, we've kissed exactly 99 times, so if we kiss for

26
00:02:06.800 --> 00:02:10.960
the hundredth time tonight, our love story is bound to last forever.

27
00:02:10.960 --> 00:02:14.000
So you don't intend to kiss Adrian until this evening?

28
00:02:14.000 --> 00:02:18.200
I got special authorization from the mayor of Paris, Mrs. Boussier, for Fire Captain

29
00:02:18.200 --> 00:02:21.800
Hessempi to put on a fireworks display, especially for the occasion.

30
00:02:21.800 --> 00:02:24.520
Wow, you really thought of everything.

31
00:02:24.520 --> 00:02:25.520
That's right.

32
00:02:25.520 --> 00:02:26.520
Love requires planning.

33
00:02:26.520 --> 00:02:29.920
Speaking of which, I've got just enough time to put tonight's meal in the fridge and make

34
00:02:29.920 --> 00:02:31.640
it to school on time.

35
00:02:31.640 --> 00:02:36.960
Oh no, this is a disaster!

36
00:02:36.960 --> 00:02:48.440
But tomorrow will be too late, Mr. Mechanic, if you don't fix it now, it'll all be a disaster!

37
00:02:48.440 --> 00:02:52.800
If I don't get tonight's meal in the fridge in time, it'll go bad and then I won't have

38
00:02:52.800 --> 00:02:55.800
anything for my evening with Adrian, which means I'll have to cancel.

39
00:02:55.800 --> 00:02:58.800
And I'll miss this once-in-a-lifetime-tonight-only-lucky-conjunction!

40
00:02:58.800 --> 00:03:03.960
Our hundredth kiss won't happen and my future love life will be ruined forever!

41
00:03:03.960 --> 00:03:07.240
Bark, on the hunt.

42
00:03:07.240 --> 00:03:11.280
That's why you have to get my scooter right now!

43
00:03:11.280 --> 00:03:12.280
Hello?

44
00:03:12.280 --> 00:03:13.640
Hello, citizen.

45
00:03:13.640 --> 00:03:17.740
I couldn't help but notice that your electric vehicle is immobilized because of a breakdown.

46
00:03:17.740 --> 00:03:24.920
I shall take it to the auto repair shop.

47
00:03:24.920 --> 00:03:26.920
Our scooter problems are fixed.

48
00:03:26.920 --> 00:03:28.920
And now, time to get these in the fridge.

49
00:03:28.920 --> 00:03:29.920
Tiki, spots on!

50
00:03:29.920 --> 00:03:38.580
Hello, sir, I need a vehicle repaired.

51
00:03:38.580 --> 00:03:39.580
Fetch!

52
00:03:39.580 --> 00:03:40.580
Hello?

53
00:03:40.580 --> 00:03:55.560
Now let's take care of your car- where did she go?

54
00:03:55.560 --> 00:04:06.900
Lay down.

55
00:04:06.900 --> 00:04:07.900
Spots off!

56
00:04:07.900 --> 00:04:10.720
Thanks to Miss Hand, you won't be late for school.

57
00:04:10.720 --> 00:04:11.720
You're right, Tiki.

58
00:04:11.720 --> 00:04:15.880
Sabrina used to be on Chloe's side doing evil things, and today she's acting for the greater

59
00:04:15.880 --> 00:04:17.880
good, helping others!

60
00:04:17.880 --> 00:04:20.880
With Sabrina, I finally succeeded where I failed with Chloe.

61
00:04:20.880 --> 00:04:24.680
You were right to entrust her with Bark's Miraculous, that was a fitting choice.

62
00:04:24.680 --> 00:04:25.680
Fitting!

63
00:04:25.680 --> 00:04:29.120
I completely forgot to take Adrian's measurements for his suit!

64
00:04:29.120 --> 00:04:32.940
My tape measure, I need my tape measure!

65
00:04:32.940 --> 00:04:35.120
I made bento dinners for tonight.

66
00:04:35.120 --> 00:04:36.120
I brought fruit tea.

67
00:04:36.120 --> 00:04:37.120
Great!

68
00:04:37.120 --> 00:04:39.960
That'll be so much better than the sugary soda we had last time.

69
00:04:39.960 --> 00:04:43.680
I found the DVD for Misumi Yuki's movie, Lone Tigress and Cub.

70
00:04:43.680 --> 00:04:46.040
Can't wait to see that movie after what you told us, Kagami.

71
00:04:46.040 --> 00:04:49.000
This is going to be the best movie night ever!

72
00:04:49.000 --> 00:04:50.000
Sorry!

73
00:04:50.000 --> 00:04:51.000
Sorry!

74
00:04:51.000 --> 00:04:52.000
Sorry!

75
00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:57.360
Oh, yeah, excuse me.

76
00:04:57.360 --> 00:04:58.360
Here comes Hurricane Marinette.

77
00:04:58.360 --> 00:04:59.360
Sorry!

78
00:04:59.360 --> 00:05:02.360
I need to borrow him for a minute.

79
00:05:02.360 --> 00:05:03.360
Hello, Marinette.

80
00:05:03.360 --> 00:05:04.360
No!

81
00:05:04.360 --> 00:05:07.320
This morning we're kissing on the cheek.

82
00:05:07.320 --> 00:05:08.320
Okay.

83
00:05:08.320 --> 00:05:09.320
But why?

84
00:05:09.320 --> 00:05:11.880
It's for a surprise.

85
00:05:11.880 --> 00:05:15.480
For our surprise evening!

86
00:05:15.480 --> 00:05:18.440
I guess this is for a surprise too, isn't it?

87
00:05:18.440 --> 00:05:20.240
There's no hiding anything from you.

88
00:05:20.240 --> 00:05:22.280
Ready for tonight, girl?

89
00:05:22.280 --> 00:05:23.280
How?

90
00:05:23.280 --> 00:05:24.280
How did you know?

91
00:05:24.280 --> 00:05:26.720
Marinette, our girls' movie night is every first Wednesday of the month.

92
00:05:26.720 --> 00:05:27.960
Of course we know about it.

93
00:05:27.960 --> 00:05:31.360
And since it's at your place, there's no chance of you being late this time.

94
00:05:31.360 --> 00:05:32.360
Tonight?

95
00:05:32.360 --> 00:05:33.360
Our movie night?

96
00:05:33.360 --> 00:05:34.360
Yeah, of course!

97
00:05:34.360 --> 00:05:35.360
Duh!

98
00:05:35.360 --> 00:05:36.360
You totally forgot, didn't you?

99
00:05:36.360 --> 00:05:37.360
Not at all!

100
00:05:37.360 --> 00:05:38.360
I'll see you girls later.

101
00:05:38.360 --> 00:05:39.360
I have things to work out with Adrian.

102
00:05:39.360 --> 00:05:40.360
She totally forgot.

103
00:05:40.360 --> 00:05:41.360
Marinette.

104
00:05:41.360 --> 00:05:42.360
Marinette.

105
00:05:42.360 --> 00:05:43.360
Marinette.

106
00:05:43.360 --> 00:05:44.360
Marinette.

107
00:05:44.360 --> 00:05:55.840
Don't wait for me.

108
00:05:55.840 --> 00:06:01.200
I have something to do.

109
00:06:01.200 --> 00:06:03.480
Did you forget about movie night with your friends?

110
00:06:03.480 --> 00:06:04.480
No!

111
00:06:04.480 --> 00:06:05.480
Not at all!

112
00:06:05.480 --> 00:06:07.920
It was all part of the plan.

113
00:06:07.920 --> 00:06:09.440
It's a surprise, actually.

114
00:06:09.440 --> 00:06:11.280
It's a new concept.

115
00:06:11.280 --> 00:06:15.480
You might choose between BFFs and boyfriends when you can enjoy both at the same time.

116
00:06:15.480 --> 00:06:20.440
It'll be our very first romantic friendly evening, like a couple group thing.

117
00:06:20.440 --> 00:06:21.440
Surprise!

118
00:06:21.440 --> 00:06:25.280
I'm not coming, Marinette.

119
00:06:25.280 --> 00:06:26.280
What?

120
00:06:26.280 --> 00:06:29.680
Everything okay, Sabrina?

121
00:06:29.680 --> 00:06:32.640
If you need to talk.

122
00:06:32.640 --> 00:06:39.240
It's just that I've lost my only friend, even though I know Chloe didn't really care about

123
00:06:39.240 --> 00:06:40.240
me.

124
00:06:40.240 --> 00:06:45.440
Now I'm trying to make new ones, but I just can't seem to.

125
00:06:45.440 --> 00:06:50.800
When I see all of you, it's clear to me that I don't belong in your group, and why would

126
00:06:50.800 --> 00:06:51.800
I?

127
00:06:51.800 --> 00:06:53.640
I was so mean to everyone.

128
00:06:53.640 --> 00:06:58.640
Deep down, I always knew none of it was right, but I genuinely love Chloe.

129
00:06:58.640 --> 00:07:02.880
I thought she'd change eventually.

130
00:07:02.880 --> 00:07:07.240
I know it took me too long to find the courage to stand up to her, and now I'm paying the

131
00:07:07.240 --> 00:07:08.560
price.

132
00:07:08.560 --> 00:07:13.280
You girls will always see me as Chloe Bourgeois' minion.

133
00:07:13.280 --> 00:07:18.080
Maybe I should leave, go to a different school, just like she did.

134
00:07:18.080 --> 00:07:21.240
There's no way you're changing school, Sabrina.

135
00:07:21.240 --> 00:07:23.440
You're not Chloe's minion anymore.

136
00:07:23.440 --> 00:07:25.640
I know how much courage it took.

137
00:07:25.640 --> 00:07:27.360
I can see that.

138
00:07:27.360 --> 00:07:30.840
Would you like to come to a movie night at Marinette's?

139
00:07:30.840 --> 00:07:32.600
Marinette would never want me there.

140
00:07:32.600 --> 00:07:34.760
She was Chloe's favorite victim.

141
00:07:34.760 --> 00:07:37.440
We bullied her for years.

142
00:07:37.440 --> 00:07:38.920
Marinette is a great girl.

143
00:07:38.920 --> 00:07:41.080
Trust me, she'll say yes.

144
00:07:41.080 --> 00:07:42.640
Are you sure?

145
00:07:42.640 --> 00:07:47.560
Here, you want one?

146
00:07:47.560 --> 00:07:48.560
Thanks.

147
00:07:48.560 --> 00:07:55.800
What do you mean you're not coming?

148
00:07:55.800 --> 00:07:59.000
When you decide to do things with people, it's to spend time with just them.

149
00:07:59.000 --> 00:08:02.440
I'm not sure your girls' movie night would feel special to them if I was there for a

150
00:08:02.440 --> 00:08:04.280
romantic evening at the same time.

151
00:08:04.280 --> 00:08:05.600
That's why I'm not coming.

152
00:08:05.600 --> 00:08:07.720
You can focus on being with just them.

153
00:08:07.720 --> 00:08:10.600
We'll have our special evening together some other time.

154
00:08:10.600 --> 00:08:11.600
Don't worry.

155
00:08:11.600 --> 00:08:12.600
No.

156
00:08:12.600 --> 00:08:13.600
No kiss.

157
00:08:13.600 --> 00:08:14.600
Not now.

158
00:08:14.600 --> 00:08:15.600
Sorry?

159
00:08:15.600 --> 00:08:16.600
Sorry.

160
00:08:16.600 --> 00:08:17.600
I have to go to the bathroom.

161
00:08:17.600 --> 00:08:18.600
Oh no!

162
00:08:18.600 --> 00:08:19.600
This is an absolute disaster!

163
00:08:19.600 --> 00:08:20.600
If Adrian doesn't come over tonight, there will never be a hundredth kiss conjunction,

164
00:08:20.600 --> 00:08:21.600
or a wedding, or house, or hamsters named Marinette!

165
00:08:21.600 --> 00:08:22.600
No!

166
00:08:22.600 --> 00:08:36.120
It took so long to get here.

167
00:08:36.120 --> 00:08:38.040
It could not end like this.

168
00:08:38.040 --> 00:08:42.400
I have to find a way to convince them to come over tonight despite the girls being there.

169
00:08:42.400 --> 00:08:43.400
Of course!

170
00:08:43.400 --> 00:08:49.400
If they were okay with this, I'm sure I could change Adrian's mind.

171
00:08:49.400 --> 00:09:00.960
Hey girls, I was thinking about tonight.

172
00:09:00.960 --> 00:09:03.960
Would you mind if we invited one more person over?

173
00:09:03.960 --> 00:09:04.960
Totally.

174
00:09:04.960 --> 00:09:06.240
Expanding our group is a cool idea.

175
00:09:06.240 --> 00:09:09.720
I was actually thinking of inviting Hagley one of these days.

176
00:09:09.720 --> 00:09:10.960
And Sublime too.

177
00:09:10.960 --> 00:09:11.960
And on Dean.

178
00:09:11.960 --> 00:09:12.960
Awesome!

179
00:09:12.960 --> 00:09:13.960
Then I'll invite Sabrina.

180
00:09:13.960 --> 00:09:19.760
I mean, there's already a lot of us and Marinette's room is so tiny.

181
00:09:19.760 --> 00:09:20.760
Should we have enough beds?

182
00:09:20.760 --> 00:09:24.080
And honestly, after everything she and Chloe did to us...

183
00:09:24.080 --> 00:09:26.880
Girls, Chloe was the problem.

184
00:09:26.880 --> 00:09:29.200
Well, Sabrina was her hench-girl.

185
00:09:29.200 --> 00:09:32.800
But without her, we wouldn't be free from Chloe today.

186
00:09:32.800 --> 00:09:34.840
And now she's all alone.

187
00:09:34.840 --> 00:09:37.360
Yeah, I don't know.

188
00:09:37.360 --> 00:09:38.360
Ask Marinette.

189
00:09:38.360 --> 00:09:43.040
It's her place after all.

190
00:09:43.040 --> 00:09:44.040
Fair enough.

191
00:09:44.040 --> 00:09:45.040
Marinette!

192
00:09:45.040 --> 00:09:46.040
Perfect timing!

193
00:09:46.040 --> 00:09:51.000
I wanted to ask you, did you see Sabrina this morning?

194
00:09:51.000 --> 00:09:52.000
Sabrina?

195
00:09:52.000 --> 00:09:53.000
Yes, Sabrina.

196
00:09:53.000 --> 00:09:54.000
She's blossoming.

197
00:09:54.000 --> 00:09:55.000
Very independent.

198
00:09:55.000 --> 00:09:56.000
That's great.

199
00:09:56.000 --> 00:09:57.720
Actually, I'd like us to do something for her.

200
00:09:57.720 --> 00:09:58.720
Definitely.

201
00:09:58.720 --> 00:09:59.720
For sure.

202
00:09:59.720 --> 00:10:04.360
Say girls, do you mind if we have an unexpected guest joining us tonight?

203
00:10:04.360 --> 00:10:07.000
I mean, I know it's a bit awkward.

204
00:10:07.000 --> 00:10:12.320
A different sort of person who doesn't quite fit the definition of our girlfriend's group.

205
00:10:12.320 --> 00:10:13.320
Sure.

206
00:10:13.320 --> 00:10:14.800
No problem, Marinette.

207
00:10:14.800 --> 00:10:15.800
Really?

208
00:10:15.800 --> 00:10:16.800
Thank you!

209
00:10:16.800 --> 00:10:17.800
This is such a relief.

210
00:10:17.800 --> 00:10:18.800
You always care about others.

211
00:10:18.800 --> 00:10:19.800
That's your greatest quality!

212
00:10:19.800 --> 00:10:20.800
You're the best!

213
00:10:20.800 --> 00:10:21.800
Oh, stop it!

214
00:10:21.800 --> 00:10:22.800
You girls are the best!

215
00:10:22.800 --> 00:10:23.800
See you tonight!

216
00:10:23.800 --> 00:10:24.800
Ta-da!

217
00:10:24.800 --> 00:10:25.800
Good news!

218
00:10:25.800 --> 00:10:26.800
You're officially invited to our girls' movie night!

219
00:10:26.800 --> 00:10:27.800
Thank you, Zoe!

220
00:10:27.800 --> 00:10:28.800
You have no idea what this means to me!

221
00:10:28.800 --> 00:10:29.800
I told you Marinette was a great girl.

222
00:10:29.800 --> 00:10:43.440
You're a great girl too.

223
00:10:43.440 --> 00:10:49.600
Okay, you're right.

224
00:10:49.600 --> 00:10:52.160
It doesn't make sense to go back and forth between the patio and the room.

225
00:10:52.160 --> 00:10:55.680
I'll just stay with you and watch the movie on my phone.

226
00:10:55.680 --> 00:10:59.360
Marinette, this thirty-seventh idea isn't going to change my mind either.

227
00:10:59.360 --> 00:11:01.180
But the girls agreed.

228
00:11:01.180 --> 00:11:05.280
No matter how you plan it, you won't really be with your girlfriends or with me.

229
00:11:05.280 --> 00:11:06.280
Let's just see each other tomorrow.

230
00:11:06.280 --> 00:11:07.280
It's no big deal.

231
00:11:07.280 --> 00:11:08.280
Enjoy your evening with your friends.

232
00:11:08.280 --> 00:11:09.280
Thank you, Marinette!

233
00:11:09.280 --> 00:11:10.280
Uh, you're welcome.

234
00:11:10.280 --> 00:11:11.280
Hurry, Dad!

235
00:11:11.280 --> 00:11:17.280
I've got to get my PJs, my toothbrush, my eye drops, and Toot Toot whistle.

236
00:11:17.280 --> 00:11:30.320
I've been invited to Marinette's house tonight.

237
00:11:30.320 --> 00:11:32.080
That's great news, sweetheart.

238
00:11:32.080 --> 00:11:34.520
You can count on your daddy to be on time.

239
00:11:34.520 --> 00:11:46.960
I just don't get the connection between these petals and Japanese cinema.

240
00:11:46.960 --> 00:11:49.280
Everything doesn't add up.

241
00:11:49.280 --> 00:11:51.920
Still no sign of Adrian.

242
00:11:51.920 --> 00:11:52.920
What's poppin', Marinette?

243
00:11:52.920 --> 00:11:53.920
Nothing!

244
00:11:53.920 --> 00:11:54.920
Nothing is poppin'.

245
00:11:54.920 --> 00:11:55.920
Then why aren't you with us already?

246
00:11:55.920 --> 00:11:56.920
Ha!

247
00:11:56.920 --> 00:11:57.920
He told me he wasn't coming, but he did anyway!

248
00:11:57.920 --> 00:11:58.920
He wanted to surprise me!

249
00:11:58.920 --> 00:11:59.920
I knew it!

250
00:11:59.920 --> 00:12:00.920
Sabrina?!

251
00:12:00.920 --> 00:12:01.920
What are you doing here?

252
00:12:01.920 --> 00:12:02.920
I'm here for movie night?

253
00:12:02.920 --> 00:12:03.920
But who invited you?

254
00:12:03.920 --> 00:12:04.920
You did.

255
00:12:04.920 --> 00:12:05.920
What?

256
00:12:05.920 --> 00:12:20.360
No, I invited Adrian, you didn't see him in the stairway, did you?

257
00:12:20.360 --> 00:12:22.200
No, it's just me.

258
00:12:22.200 --> 00:12:25.960
This is a disaster!

259
00:12:25.960 --> 00:12:33.120
Sorry Marinette, I probably should go then.

260
00:12:33.120 --> 00:12:36.200
Something can be done.

261
00:12:36.200 --> 00:12:41.640
Do you know how to make the Hoatan star return to Jupiter another day?

262
00:12:41.640 --> 00:13:03.840
Then no, nothing can be done.

263
00:13:03.840 --> 00:13:10.000
Dad, can you please come get me?

264
00:13:10.000 --> 00:13:13.080
Weren't you supposed to be sleeping at your friend's house?

265
00:13:13.080 --> 00:13:15.120
There's no place for me.

266
00:13:15.120 --> 00:13:20.320
Not at Marinette's house, not at the school, not in this city!

267
00:13:20.320 --> 00:13:23.880
Don't move sweetheart, I'm coming right now!

268
00:13:23.880 --> 00:13:27.040
Wait, wait, wait.

269
00:13:27.040 --> 00:13:29.480
You invited Adrian to our sleepover?

270
00:13:29.480 --> 00:13:34.360
The hundredth kiss, the fireworks, the stars, it could only happen tonight!

271
00:13:34.360 --> 00:13:35.360
Without asking us?

272
00:13:35.360 --> 00:13:36.360
But I did!

273
00:13:36.360 --> 00:13:41.080
I told you about it earlier, you only agreed to it, but it looks like you didn't change

274
00:13:41.080 --> 00:13:42.880
his mind and now everything is ruined.

275
00:13:42.880 --> 00:13:44.880
I don't get it.

276
00:13:44.880 --> 00:13:58.120
If Adrian was the surprise guest, but it wasn't him at the door, then who was?

277
00:13:58.120 --> 00:14:02.120
Sabrina!

278
00:14:02.120 --> 00:14:03.120
Hello!

279
00:14:03.120 --> 00:14:08.880
Forgive my intrusion, but I sense a great deal of guilt preventing you from making friends.

280
00:14:08.880 --> 00:14:09.880
No!

281
00:14:09.880 --> 00:14:12.880
I'm coming sweetheart!

282
00:14:12.880 --> 00:14:14.880
Hello!

283
00:14:14.880 --> 00:14:25.680
Forgive my intrusion, but I sense the pain of a father helpless in the face of his daughter's

284
00:14:25.680 --> 00:14:26.680
sorrow.

285
00:14:26.680 --> 00:14:30.960
If you wish, I can give you the power to allow people to see your daughter the way you see

286
00:14:30.960 --> 00:14:31.960
her.

287
00:14:31.960 --> 00:14:32.960
What do you think?

288
00:14:32.960 --> 00:14:36.480
I must fix this miscarriage of justice.

289
00:14:36.480 --> 00:14:38.360
And what should I call you?

290
00:14:38.360 --> 00:14:39.360
Daddy Kong!

291
00:14:39.360 --> 00:14:40.360
Sabrina!

292
00:14:40.360 --> 00:14:41.360
Come back!

293
00:14:41.360 --> 00:14:42.360
This is a misunderstanding!

294
00:14:42.360 --> 00:14:43.360
You!

295
00:14:43.360 --> 00:14:44.360
Freeze!

296
00:14:44.360 --> 00:14:48.680
In the name of love, I'm arresting you for moral damage to my daughter!

297
00:14:48.680 --> 00:14:49.680
No, Dad!

298
00:14:49.680 --> 00:14:50.680
It wasn't their fault!

299
00:14:50.680 --> 00:15:10.040
You're finally going to see my Sabrina as I see her, through the eyes of love!

300
00:15:10.040 --> 00:15:14.420
You only love me because you were forced to!

301
00:15:14.420 --> 00:15:15.420
Sabrina!

302
00:15:15.420 --> 00:15:16.420
Oh no!

303
00:15:16.420 --> 00:15:17.600
This is a major disaster for real!

304
00:15:17.600 --> 00:15:18.600
Tiki!

305
00:15:18.600 --> 00:15:19.600
Spots on!

306
00:15:19.600 --> 00:15:20.600
More!

307
00:15:20.600 --> 00:15:21.600
More love for my daughter!

308
00:15:21.600 --> 00:15:22.600
Sabrina!

309
00:15:22.600 --> 00:15:23.600
We love you!

310
00:15:23.600 --> 00:15:24.600
No!

311
00:15:24.600 --> 00:15:25.600
Leave me alone!

312
00:15:25.600 --> 00:15:26.600
Give me back my daughter right now!

313
00:15:26.600 --> 00:15:27.600
Emergency evacuation service!

314
00:15:27.600 --> 00:15:28.600
Sabrina!

315
00:15:28.600 --> 00:15:49.880
We love you!

316
00:15:49.880 --> 00:15:50.880
I feel for you.

317
00:15:50.880 --> 00:15:52.680
I have the same problem with my fan club.

318
00:15:52.680 --> 00:15:53.680
Give her back!

319
00:15:53.680 --> 00:15:54.680
Candelar!

320
00:15:54.680 --> 00:15:57.520
Create a diversion while I get Sabrina to safety!

321
00:15:57.520 --> 00:15:59.200
I love being a distraction.

322
00:15:59.200 --> 00:16:00.200
Power up!

323
00:16:00.200 --> 00:16:01.200
Tanaquism!

324
00:16:01.200 --> 00:16:18.880
Sabrina Rinconpria, I'm going to need Ms. Hound's help.

325
00:16:18.880 --> 00:16:22.040
Ladybug, I don't deserve that Miraculous.

326
00:16:22.040 --> 00:16:23.440
I'm an awful person.

327
00:16:23.440 --> 00:16:26.680
I'm not worthy of being part of the Miraculars.

328
00:16:26.680 --> 00:16:28.720
It's like I'm not worthy of having friends.

329
00:16:28.720 --> 00:16:34.640
Sabrina, the reason I gave you the dog Miraculous is because I know you're a good person.

330
00:16:34.640 --> 00:16:35.900
You've already changed.

331
00:16:35.900 --> 00:16:39.400
You just can't see it yourself yet.

332
00:16:39.400 --> 00:16:41.840
Visualize the Sabrina you've become.

333
00:16:41.840 --> 00:16:49.880
The one you want everyone to see.

334
00:16:49.880 --> 00:17:13.480
That's incredible!

335
00:17:13.480 --> 00:17:14.480
You're incredible.

336
00:17:14.480 --> 00:17:15.480
I'm enforcing the law!

337
00:17:15.480 --> 00:17:26.240
You better get new glasses or learn how to aim, Daddy Cop.

338
00:17:26.240 --> 00:17:28.040
I'll take care of him if you will.

339
00:17:28.040 --> 00:17:29.040
Turn around.

340
00:17:29.040 --> 00:17:30.680
But I'll crash into him.

341
00:17:30.680 --> 00:17:42.000
Just trust me.

342
00:17:42.000 --> 00:17:45.740
It's time for you to seize Cat Noir's Miraculous, dear Daddy Cop.

343
00:17:45.740 --> 00:17:46.740
Lucky charm!

344
00:17:46.740 --> 00:17:47.740
Thank you, m'lady.

345
00:17:47.740 --> 00:17:55.320
Go recharge and then head to the Mulah Auto Repair Shop.

346
00:17:55.320 --> 00:18:00.240
We're going to organize a little surprise for Daddy Cop.

347
00:18:00.240 --> 00:18:02.040
Where's my daughter, you outlaw?

348
00:18:02.040 --> 00:18:03.520
What have you done with her?

349
00:18:03.520 --> 00:18:22.920
You'll have to catch me if you want to know.

350
00:18:22.920 --> 00:18:26.000
Guess this game's gonna have to wait.

351
00:18:26.000 --> 00:18:30.160
Whoa, awesome new get-up, Miss Hound.

352
00:18:30.160 --> 00:18:37.240
Hinks, Cosmo Bug is going to need us.

353
00:18:37.240 --> 00:18:44.400
Are you ready?

354
00:18:44.400 --> 00:18:51.400
In position!

355
00:18:51.400 --> 00:18:56.400
Now!

356
00:18:56.400 --> 00:19:01.280
Cataclysm!

357
00:19:01.280 --> 00:19:06.200
Retrogradation!

358
00:19:06.200 --> 00:19:19.240
No more evil doing for you, little Akuma.

359
00:19:19.240 --> 00:19:24.400
Time to de-evilize!

360
00:19:24.400 --> 00:19:25.400
Gotcha!

361
00:19:25.400 --> 00:19:28.440
Miraculous Linneybug!

362
00:19:28.440 --> 00:19:45.480
It's great that you want to look after your daughter's well-being, Officer, but you don't

363
00:19:45.480 --> 00:19:47.000
have to worry anymore.

364
00:19:47.000 --> 00:19:49.880
Sabrina has it in her to make it on her own.

365
00:19:49.880 --> 00:19:53.200
Probably because she has such a great dad.

366
00:19:53.200 --> 00:19:54.920
Found it!

367
00:19:54.920 --> 00:19:57.200
Dark Wings Baw.

368
00:19:57.200 --> 00:20:02.600
Are you sure this is all really necessary?

369
00:20:02.600 --> 00:20:03.600
Silence!

370
00:20:03.600 --> 00:20:07.760
I ordered you not to address me, Kwami.

371
00:20:07.760 --> 00:20:11.280
Now let's start again.

372
00:20:11.280 --> 00:20:12.820
Are you sure everything's okay?

373
00:20:12.820 --> 00:20:13.820
Don't worry, Mr. Register.

374
00:20:13.820 --> 00:20:14.820
We'll take good care of her.

375
00:20:14.820 --> 00:20:18.040
Have a nice evening, Daddy dear.

376
00:20:18.040 --> 00:20:20.720
Thank you again for inviting me, Marinette.

377
00:20:20.720 --> 00:20:23.840
I want to take this time to apologize to all of you.

378
00:20:23.840 --> 00:20:27.480
I know I wasn't always nice to you girls, but I've changed.

379
00:20:27.480 --> 00:20:35.920
And if you'll accept me, of course I'd be happy and proud to be your friend.

380
00:20:35.920 --> 00:20:36.920
Everyone makes mistakes.

381
00:20:36.920 --> 00:20:39.860
Besides, you were a victim of Chloe, too.

382
00:20:39.860 --> 00:20:43.080
You were very brave separating yourself from her.

383
00:20:43.080 --> 00:20:45.880
And I, too, want to apologize.

384
00:20:45.880 --> 00:20:50.680
I've been focusing so much on my relationship with Adrien that I forgot to give my attention

385
00:20:50.680 --> 00:20:53.440
to the ones who really needed it.

386
00:20:53.440 --> 00:20:56.900
I promise I'll be more attentive from now on.

387
00:20:56.900 --> 00:21:01.900
Welcome, Sabrina.

388
00:21:01.900 --> 00:21:15.080
Yes, I told you.

389
00:21:15.080 --> 00:21:18.920
I like it, Sabrina.

390
00:21:18.920 --> 00:21:19.920
Wow!

391
00:21:19.920 --> 00:21:23.040
Your new look is awesome!

392
00:21:23.040 --> 00:21:24.040
You think so?

393
00:21:24.040 --> 00:21:29.040
Oh, by the way, I forgot something.

394
00:21:29.040 --> 00:21:30.040
100.

395
00:21:30.040 --> 00:21:37.760
I wanted to save it for our special evening but, Liane, I realized that we don't need

396
00:21:37.760 --> 00:21:41.720
a conjunction or fireworks to love each other.

397
00:21:41.720 --> 00:21:42.720
101.

398
00:21:42.720 --> 00:21:56.200
What's up, Cockroach?

399
00:21:56.200 --> 00:21:57.680
Leave me alone, Ray.

400
00:21:57.680 --> 00:21:58.680
What's the matter?

401
00:21:58.680 --> 00:22:05.720
Are you afraid I'll show your new friends who you really are?

402
00:22:05.720 --> 00:22:09.720
The nice thing about the digital world is that nothing ever disappears.

403
00:22:09.720 --> 00:22:14.600
Just like who you were back in NYC, right, Cockroach?

404
00:22:14.600 --> 00:22:41.640
I'm sorry, Ray.

405
00:22:41.640 --> 00:22:51.080
I'm sorry.
